- Install vcenter and click on run
- Click on vcsa installer and click on install.
- Select Deploy vCenter -> Next -> I accept -> Next
- Type your esxiâ€™s ip address and username as root and password then click Yes
- Give a name and password
- Select Tiny - 14gb ram
-  Enable thin disk -> Next
- Select DHCP -> Next -> Finish
- When Installation is at 80% go to Browser and login to vmware esxi access page. 
- Type the user name and password.
- In vm  Run the Vcenterâ€™s VM. 
- Once the Stage 1 Installation completed click on Continue.
- Give your domain name and credentials and click Next and Ok
- installation will take 10 mintues, then click close
- Open a new tab in browser and type the ip which occurred on completion wizard.
- Navigate to vcenter appliance via ip in browser
- Right click on ip address->New Datacenter
- Give region name as BOMBAY_REGION 
-  Right click on BOMBAY_REGION and select cluster 
- Put ip address of your esxi server 
- Type root a username and give a password and click Next
- Select Evaluation License -> Next -> Disabled -> Next
- In VM location select BOMBAY_REGION and Next
- Click on vSphere Client and Select Licensing. 
- type the license key and select Next and Finish
- Navigate to host configure->Time Configuration Click on ADD SERVICE
- Type esxi ip address. 
- In Vcenter management -> time servers -> enter ip address and select time zone







